<br>
Druids don't even really want to be as good as Clerics in xp groups.  I think the majority of the Druids here agree that healing needs a revamp and Clerics need an upgrade to Divine Light.  Point is this is a Druid petition therefor we are addressing Druid issues which in the end game boils down to the roll that Druids are assigned in raids, healing. <br>
<br>
Clerics should be full force on the side of this petition because we are asking (forcing) VI to take a look at the effectiveness of all heals vs aoe raid effect.  AOE's were put in to counterbalance Complete Healing which has a trivializing effect on all end game raid mobs. With Lucin VI has turned from the belief that all they must do to make encounters more difficult is to upgrade the number of hitpoints a mob has or hits for allowing both VI and raid forces to be more creative in the end game balance.  Clerics need diversity but as long as they steadfastly have a strangle hold on Raid healing via CH they will be considered godly and balanced.  Once healing is looked at and spread out among the 3 priest classes more evenly, VI will have a reason to give Clerics the diversity they crave.<br>
<br>
I would recommend that instead of Clerics coming here and saying no to our petition what they should be doing is collectively forming their own petition showing where CH has forced Clerics to be keyholded into being Raid Bots.  Focusing on the issues that effect clerics in end game group situations. An increase to the MOK line that would have varying effects but not stack with one another so that they would be situational would be great for Clerics.  Ask for a self only invis post 50.  There are many things that are tagged undead that are very good for end game xp groups but the last dot recieved is at lvl 52 and the damage ratio on it is laughable vs other classes dots increases in dps on cleric undead dots would not only give a variable role in groups but also give a limited solo ability.  Clerics also can have a valuable role in groups with their stun line a roll shared with enchanter but when a cleric is stunning the chanter can focus on mezzing increase the effects and variables on stuns. <p><CENTER>
