<br>
I think that you're starting to see the problem here.  Other than CH, clerics don't bring too much more to the table in normal situations.  It probably doesn't help that they have the least number of spells amongst the priest classes, and while I haven't looked it up lately, they did have the least number of spells alotted to them of any caster class.  So they don't bring that much utility to the table.<br>
<br>
I could also point out that right now the clerics have 5 useless spell lines (lull, PB AE DD, yaulp, wreckless strength, summoned hammer), further crippling the class, and a couple more that are only marginally useful.  As an example, you brought up stuns in your post.  The reason that most clerics don't use their stuns all that often, especially at high levels is that they are resisted heavily by mobs, which makes them almost useless in a grouping situation.  Even more so on raids.  This is why paladins are the ones using the stuns, if it lands, great.  If it doesn't, it doesn't burn up critical mana.  Oh, and as a bonus it's a heavy taunt.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Right now, the specialist class that you have to compete for in groups is gimped.  Which I believe will be the thing that will kill this petition.  As long as the specialist has to work with mostly gimped spells, each time that they look at balancing to see what's fair, they'll look at the specialist and give you less.<br>
<br>
I know it sucks, and the clerics should probably from one of their own, but for the most part, their aren't really all that many people that I've seen who still play a cleric as a primary character.  Most now are alts that people play on raids because they are needed.<br>
<br>
Oh, well. *shrug* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukiatek2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kiatek2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/15/02 7:25:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=711>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:A compromise</span><hr size=1> I still dont think alot of people that are coming here to post that druids either dont need change or if we are changed will depose other classes understand something.  You keep saying that if we are changed you should be changed.  Read this again:<br>
