<br>
Guess what the remaining clerics and Druids got to do?  Each Druid or alt cleric had a MT cleric targeted, and was not allowed to change targets or do anything else but heal the cleric after Mod rods were used.  <br>
<br>
Avatar of War is an extreme case of this, because it hits so hard (One of the MTs was only up for about 30% health loss on AoW, and took 130,000 dmg) but this shows you the usefulness of a Druid on such raids.  <br>
(We did get AoW though, 4 blades of carnage)<br>
<br>
Anyway, all those skills so heavily flaunted by every other class, DS, DD, Buffs, Ports, etc-useless.  If there had been enough clerics the Druids wouldn't have even been healing.<br>
<br>
Druids are said to be good at filling the gaps in a raid, extra DD if you don't have enough, spot healing, etc.  The problem is that as guilds get more powerful, get more of the specialized classes that do these things better than Druids, Druids lose their backup spots.  If you have 20 raiding clerics, which the guild I raid with does, you hardly need Druid healing, and if you have Druids healing you hope to be in a group with a cleric not healing MT.  If you have 5 raiding shammies, 8 raiding wizards, etc, you need the Druids to fill in less and less.  Weaker guilds are more accepting of Druids, because they have deficiencies-I.e those things Druids are number 2-4 rank in.  A guild with only 1 wizard may bring Druids along for the DD, as well as ports out.  A guild with less than one cleric per raiding group will bring a Druid along for healing.  A guild with a cleric per group with 2 clerics to spare will shrug at a Druid.  A guild with enough firepower will still allow Druids to DD, but won't really care if they do or not.  <br>
<br>
There is one final aspect I want to mention.  When equipment from raids is limited, only a certain number of drops.  Who do you think is going to get the items?  The cleric, who you KNOW you need.  The (insert class here for the all all items), or perhaps give it to that Druid, who you didn't care if they were DDing or not.  I saw a Druid (only high end loot I ever saw given to Druid, although it does happen) who got belt from King Tormax.  The Druid didn't know what to do..she was surprised.  From the way she reacted, I don't think she had ever been looting from an Uber mob before.  She had been 60 for many months by then too, so she wasn't some 51 newb on her first raid.  <br>
<br>
In short, as guilds do get better and better, Druids get left behind for not being best at anything.  I don't even think these changes will be enough to make Druids truly useful in the fully end game, but it will certainly help then fill in those gaps a little bit longer.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf Elemental</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/15/02 2:47:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=713>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conversation: What about Us! (State of The Druid)</span><hr size=1> Regarding the 5 &quot;useless&quot; lines, a couple jumped out at me.<br>
<br>
Lull.  Yes, resists suck, especially on the first mob.  However, it is better than nothing.  In an xp grind situation, a cleric is a good candidate for the puller job.  Tools available to the cleric include lull, stuns, root, atone, da/db, not to mention a full suit of plate armor.  Like druids, clerics provide buffs, heals, and bursts of damage, which leaves them free to leave the group without slowing down kills.<br>
<br>
PB AE DD.  Well, this, along with great heals and hitpoint buffs can get a cleric into an AE group.  DA/DB mean the cleric can pull, especially in places with harmtouching mobs.<br>
<br>
A couple of my favorite things are pulling, and AE groups.  Clerics are well equipped for both jobs, IMO.  Indoors, I think clerics can make better pullers than druids (given equal amounts of pulling experience.)  Outdoors, druids are probably better, but clerics are perfectly capable of grabbing Umbrous_Toiler578 or Shissar_Revenant129.<br>
<br>
I have a question for the &quot;You must pay&quot; crowd.  (The philosophy is basically: druids are overpowered early, and thus deserve to be weaker in later stages of the game.)  Does that philosophy apply to classes that are godlike in the current end game, but &quot;need work&quot; in the early/mid game as well?  Would there be such vehement objections to Ports to Temples for clerics, or a re-tuning of wizard rain spells in the lower levels so that they could maintain higher damage output in groups?  I hope not.  I think fixes like that would make the game more enjoyable for all.  <br>
<br>
-Quelm, Hierophant<br>
