<br>
First and foremost, I feel the druid class is one of the best in the game.  They still remain versatile and such.  I do play a druid on a different server.  Granted, she is only level 17 right now.  I do however notice the significant difference in healing, mana pool, and damage of their nukes.  I am doing more with the druid than I was doing as a wizard of the same level.<br>
<br>
1.  Port to Luclin.<br>
<br>
Think about what you are saying.  You sare saying, you want druid to be able to port to a foreign land away from the 'mother' Norrath.  I am not flaming you, but think about what you are saying.  Why would druids be able to port to Luclin in the first place?  First of all, there are no druid rings.  Second, it is not 'natural land'.  Wizards, based on the game history, have always been able to port to the moon or planes.  This is a wizard ability.  What you are suggesting will cause the same issue wizards that you are having.<br>
<br>
2.  On better nukes<br>
<br>
I am only going to dwell on this comment for a moment.  YOU WILL NEVER BE ABLE TO OUTNUKE WIZARDS.  I dont know how many times I have heard druids complain that wizards nuke better then them.  It is a class feature.  Much like the 5% bonus clerics get for healing.  You admit, you agree with the fact that clerics are the best healers.  Now admit that wizards have the best nukes.  Druids either have the 2nd or 3rd best in the game (Magicians and Druids are pretty close)<br>
<br>
-------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I few obervations.  First and foremost, I do agree that druids need a better heal.  I also agree that the spell stacking between some druid and cleric buffs needs to be corrected.<br>
<br>
Druids are not a mana efficient healer.  This is quite agreed upon.  But, the mana efficiency (and correct me if I am wrong) balance's itself out with the druid regen spells.  What is the casting time / mana on the pack regen (or the higher level).<br>
<br>
A little more on druid nukes.  The highest nuke that I know of is 1125.  This was added with the Luclin expansion.  Wizards, PRE LUCLIN, already had a 1600dmg nuke.  At this point, there was already a noticeable gap.  With Velious and Luclin, Wizards got 2kdmg nukes towards Yelinak and Tormax bloodline.  These will not work on any other dragons or giants.  Only really useful on raids.  Wizards recieved an anciant spell that does 2100dmg.  Druids will never be able to nuke for this much.  If Verant does, Wizards will start to complain<br>
<br>
On manaburn:  Why stop here?  Why not at the mirror ability that necro's have?  These abilities are usable only onces every 144 RL min.  A death will not reset it.  One you use it, it is gone until the time runs out.  Not very overpowering.  Lets no mention that it drains all your mana and you must regen to full in order to start nuking again.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Druids do need work, I will agree with you on that part.  But making the arguement, 'Well, so_and_so_class had this and that' is going to get you nowhere.  Each class has its place and use on a raid or group.  Druids will never heal as well as clerics, druids will never nuke as good as wizards.  Druids are the second best at these things and should not overstep that line.<br>
<br>
What druids do need:<br>
<br>
*a better mana efficient or effective heal<br>
*corrected buff stacking<br>
*higher level DoT (perhaps lure type dot?)<br>
<br>
