</table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugoldenblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goldenblade</A> at: 4/16/02 12:21:59 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uanaangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AnaAngel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/16/02 3:59:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=722>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/realm2/liteasair/kateicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Conversation: What about Us! (State of The Druid)</span><hr size=1> Lots of classes can solo Keg.  I know poorly (compared to end game) equipped monks, warriors, wizards, chanters, rogues, rangers, etc who have soloed to 60, if not entirely, then at least through the end of 59.  I even know a cleric that somehow managed to solo to 56, although that was probably pretty slow.  There is nothing in that list that other classes can't learn to solo, it's just that Druids had to learn how to solo to get xp.  Please excuse me while I take a moment to show you why.  <br>
<br>
In a high end group, a priest class will be healing, there is no other point for them, other classes can handle whatever tasks exist, such as snare/root.  <br>
<br>
There are several ways in which a character can &quot;heal.&quot;  <br>
1) Direct heals<br>
2) Damage prevention<br>
3) Regeneration type spells<br>
4) Killing the mobs faster<br>
<br>
If you are in a group of 5, no matter what the makeup of the group, and you have one of each priest class that are equal level LFG, who are you going to pick?  <br>
<br>
Clerics clearly have the best direct heals, that is their purpose.  Clerics can also regen tanks in the form of Mark of Karn, which is also an effect of thier ToV BP, that with one cast can regen ALL melee fighting the mob.  Clerics get a 15 point DS, Mark of Retribution, which they also can cast on a single target and get the entire group.  Clerics can undead blast for a good amount of dmg, and blast non-undead for over 700 dmg, which is a decent amount.  Clerics get the best HP/AC buffs, Aegolism is around 1300hp if I recall, and nice ac as well.  No other buffs come close to that, and their lower end buffs will still always beat any other class at the same level.  <br>
<br>
Shamans get slow, which is the single best dmg prevention spell available to any class in existance, when melee dmg is a concern.  Shaman slowed mobs allow a Shaman or Druid to heal efficiently against a normal xp mob.  Shamans also get the best melee buffs available to anyone in the game, allowing a strongly melee group to greatly increase dmg, making the mobs die all that much faster.  In an xp group, a shaman will probably not be using many of their other skills, but there are many more that are useful, even without a full spellbook.  <br>
<br>
Because my point is to explain the Druid in this post, I will take each Druid skill apart piece by piece, hopefully to show you what every 40+ Druid knows.  <br>
<br>
Damage Shields:  Maximum DS dmg is 36, mobs hit for over 100 on a regular basis post 50.  For DS to be useful you need to keep aggro on a single tank, or waste mana putting DS on several people.  DS also doesn't last very long, but this is probably the best dmg/mana ratio a Druid can get.<br>
<br>
Regen: Regen is a good friend of the Druid.  The problem is, regen doesn't last very long, and any mob you can get xp from will kill a tank much faster than regen will heal.  I believe the last regen spell a Druid gets heals for 24 every tick, (6 seconds).  Tanks in an xp group will still be taking signifcantly more dmg than this, but it's a start, and if you want to keep this on several targets, bye bye mana.  <br>
<br>
Direct Damage: Druids get some nice DD spells.  The problem is, you have as many as 5 other people in the group that do the job of your DDs, damage.  A rogue with a single backstab combo can do almost as much dmg as the best Druid blast, without using a discipline.  Other classes can do sustained manaless dmg that is essential.  At worst there are other classes with mana meant for blasting, mages/wizards come to mind.  Therefore a Druid will only use this when mana is abundant, which means never.<br>
<br>
Healing: When it comes down to it, a Druid will be using almost all of their mana to heal.  Unless C2 or C3 is available, a Druid healing in a good group will not have much mana outside of DSing one target, Regening one target, snaring mobs, and healing dmg taken.  If a rough pull, especially with no chanter, a Druid will forget about DS regen DD, in exchange for as many heals as they can manage, which means a Druid in a pinch can get relegated to a crappy version of a cleric.  (This is also the situation on most raids where mobs hit for 300+ on a regular basis, Druids spam heal someone getting hit harder than they can possibly keep up with).  <br>
<br>
Other Druid skills are easily copied by other classes.  Numerous classes have snare, no biggie there.  Quite a few classes have root as well, which can work as a snare substitute to keep mobs from running, or for some Ghetto mez.  Wizards can evac, and as mentioned above, blast better than Druids.  But when it comes down to it, how many groups would rather be evaced than just be good enough to survive without it?  <br>
I personally would take a cleric over a Druid any day, CH the tank and he is good for another couple good rounds with xpable mobs.  I would even prefer a shaman more than a cleric, 75% slow is probably the best xp spell in the game.  Heck, while we're at it, why not put a shaman and Cleric together?  Clerics easily heal the group that takes practically no dmg from mobs?  Can a Druid come close?..not really.  Should a Druid be FORCED to solo?..I would hope not, but that's the way things stand in a competative market.  6 slots in a group, you decide who you want.  And if you don't want a Druid in an xp group, what do you expect them to do on a raid where resists are high for DDs, DS is handled by mages, Regen is pointless where mobs hit for 300-1200 single swings, And the caster healing spells that Druids get still have problems healing the up to 4k hp a Necromancer can get...try healing a tank, or even a cleric after that.  <br>
<br>
Sorry if I am ranting, but Druids have a raw deal post 50, and as many can attest to, it wasn't as bad before a year ago.  It takes a smarter Druid to be able to group as well as an otherwise equal Cleric, because even the clerics who post here complain that their jobs are simple, stand up CH, sit down.  I was even in a group with an e-bay cleric in Seb, we taught her what CH was IN the group, and she still did fine.  (She had just been using the highest level heal in her 54 spellbook).  The rest of the group was good at their jobs, but still, a 60 Druid that didn't know their spells would have seen a dead group.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showMessageRange?topicID=650.topic&start=201&stop=220>11</a><a hr